15/*! \file */
16
17#include <config.h>
18
19#include <stddef.h>
20
21#include <isc/util.h>
22
23#include <dns/rdataset.h>
24#include <dns/rdatasetiter.h>
25
26void
27dns_rdatasetiter_destroy(dns_rdatasetiter_t **iteratorp) {
28 /*
29 * Destroy '*iteratorp'.
30 */
31
32 REQUIRE(iteratorp != NULL);
33 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASETITER_VALID(*iteratorp));
34
35 (*iteratorp)->methods->destroy(iteratorp);
36
37 ENSURE(*iteratorp == NULL);
38}
39
40isc_result_t
41dns_rdatasetiter_first(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator) {
42 /*
43 * Move the rdataset cursor to the first rdataset at the node (if any).
44 */
45
46 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASETITER_VALID(iterator));
47
48 return (iterator->methods->first(iterator));
49}
50
51isc_result_t
52dns_rdatasetiter_next(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator) {
53 /*
54 * Move the rdataset cursor to the next rdataset at the node (if any).
55 */
56
57 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASETITER_VALID(iterator));
58
59 return (iterator->methods->next(iterator));
60}
61
62void
63dns_rdatasetiter_current(dns_rdatasetiter_t *iterator,
64 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset)
65{
66 /*
67 * Return the current rdataset.
68 */
69
70 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASETITER_VALID(iterator));
71 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
72 REQUIRE(! dns_rdataset_isassociated(rdataset));
73
74 iterator->methods->current(iterator, rdataset);
75}
